  <front>
   <head>ACROSTIC ON MISS [SALLY CLARKE]. 1768.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">SERAPHIC Virgins of the tuneful Choir,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Assist me to prepare the sounding lyre!</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Like her I sing, soft, sensible, and fair,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Let the smooth numbers warble in the air;</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Ye Prudes, Coquets, and all the misled throng,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Can Beauty, Virtue, Sense, demand the Song;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Look then on Clarke, and see them all unite;</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">A beauteous pattern, to the always-right.</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Rest here, my Muse, not soar above thy sphere,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Kings might pay adoration to the fair,</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="12">Enchanting, full of joy, peerless in face and air.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
